entry.title: formulanimations :: a procedural animation
entry.content:
formulanimations :: a procedural animation
Made this one quickly during two live coding session in Shadertoy (www.shadertoy.com). The key was to try some procedural walk system which, unlike other procedural animation systems, stateless, would be just as implicit function of time. The creature walks over the terrain and adapts to it. I didn't add secondary body motions to make it more real or anything. In fact, most visual aspects in the image are unfinished: shading is broken in the creature and stretched in the stones, the body shape is too simple (it's a sphere + cosinus!!), the eyes don't connect to the body, the sky is flat, the animation has no secondary motions as said, and there aren't camera effects. BUT I got stop here and move on. It looks okeish I think (for being a web-browser based raymarched formula, that is!). The source code is here: https://www.shadertoy.com/view/Mss3zM
